Ask HN: Japanese Culture Resources
text:
I am quite fascinated with parts of the Japanese culture. Their life-long striving for perfection, as seen in Jiro's dream of sushi. The mentality that keeps businesses going through generations, for hundreds of years. The concept of repairing as adding to the beauty instead of subtracting.

But I have not found interesting blogs, webpages, podcasts or books that cover this broadly. I am sure they are there, I just have not found them.

A bonus would be anything related to photography or motorcycles. But for lack of more precise description I am probably more interested in the philosophy than concrete subjects.

So if you have anything you think might fit that broad description, then I would be very interested.
